A Census of Edge-Transitive Tetravalent Graphs
collection.complete: There are three kinds of edge-transitive tetravalent graphs, namely: dart-transitive, half-arc-transitive and semisymmetric. This Census inherits completeness in the first two categories from studies by Potočnik, Spiga and Verret. The third category is not known to be complete and we strongly suspect that it is not.
collection.FAIR_summary: The paper (part of the metadata) is not yet published (January 2019).  Every graph has a unique identifier (C4[n, i]), an encyclopedic page (the URL is deducible from its identifier).  The dataset is available as a Magma file and the properties as an Excel file.
